subSubSection.paragraph:
Type D.
It represents a morphological variety of scales which is almost entirely composed of rhomboidal and elongated central areas. The lateral areas are very narrow (
Fig. 8H
) or are not developed at all (
Fig. 8I
). The lateral crown walls are smooth.
